<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-11-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="259" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hicks</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-11-17"><hi rend="italic">November 17,
                                    1891</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 182.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 318 of the 26th
                            ultimo, reporting the adjournment of the Congress of Peru without taking
                            action upon the claim of the Hydrographic Commission.</p>
                        <p>You may express the regret of the Department that payment of this
                            admittedly just obligation of Peru should be so indefinitely
                            postponed.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>